content:
'file' is not a valid Win32 resource file

This error occurs when you specify a filename with the /win32res compiler option that is not a valid or correctly formatted Win32 resource file. In Visual Studio, the filename is specified in the Application pane of the Project Designer.

See Also

Application Page, Project Designer (C#)
